            "subtype": "ability",
            "text": "When a bee borer hits a target larger than itself, its legs attach it to that creature. While attached, the bee borer moves with the creature. The bee borer and the creature it's attached to are both off-guard. The borer remains attached until the creature dies or Escapes (DC 19).",
